article.headline: South Florida 64, Valparaiso 62
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Bradley Mosley scored 16 points and led South Florida on a second-half comeback to defeat Valparaiso 64-62 on Tuesday night. Mosley scored 12 of his points after halftime, including a layup with just more than a minute left to give South Florida (2-0) its winning margin. Mosley also put in six points during an 18-6 Bulls run to overcome a 43-32 Valparaiso lead early in the second half. The Crusaders (1-2) had the ball at the end of the game, but Ali Berdiel missed a shot at the buzzer that could have tied the game. Joaquim Gomes led Valparaiso with 13 points and Jimmie Miles added 10 off the bench. Terrence Leather had a double-double with 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Bulls, which dominated the rebounding battle 40-27. The Bulls' second half comeback was fueled by hot shooting. After hitting only 38 percent of their shots in the first half, the Bulls shot 54 percent after half time.
